ETTA LISSY v. HERMAN LISSY ETTA LISSY v. HERMAN LISSY, t/a WYMAN PARK MARKET. [Nos. 36 and 37,

October Term, 1941.]

Decided December 3, 1941.

*690The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Sloan, Johnson, Delaplaine, Collins, Forsythe, and Mar-BURY, JJ.

Michael J. Manley, with whom was William O. Tydings on the brief, for the appellant. Webster S. Blades, with whom were Blades & Rosenfeld on the brief, for the appellee. Collins, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court
